    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001/11–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1458. Re ur 1137 Nov 28, Dept perceives no objection to use of travel affidavits
                    for such members of Li’s party as appear to be accompanying him in connection
                    with stated purpose of visit. Since Pres Li has made it known on several
                    occasions that sole purpose of trip which wld <pb facs="0625" n="615"
                        xml:id="pg_615"/> be of limited duration is medical treatment, Dept fails
                    perceive close connection with this objective of such members of his party as
                    former Min of Interior and Li’s Chief of Polit Bureau and wld desire
                    satisfactory clarification this point before authorizing issuance visas these
                    two.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
